<paragraph id="99FF993667FAC19082736FBB4C260FAC" pageId="14" pageNumber="83">Type.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9439B5AC74A0B11ACBF116CC709BB968" pageId="14" pageNumber="83">
Iran. 60 km north of Dizful, 3 May 1937, 
<emphasis id="28B16A104822DABFD84A63B410926F07" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="83">
M. 
<normalizedToken id="6FFDC31969479B6D7CC915BAE48D6E75" originalValue="Köie">Koeie</normalizedToken>
475
</emphasis>
(lectotype, 
<emphasis id="DB885430C2D9348EB199930608D219D5" bold="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="83">here designated</emphasis>
: C [C10016935 image!]; isolectotype: LE).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="6AE16B133B6ACA0A7308A06436C819B6" pageId="14" pageNumber="83" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="1E74C683A50DD119EF6E98555E537E93" pageId="14" pageNumber="83">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6C2374B104FC2DE075C2F8536F28A3E2" pageId="14" pageNumber="83">Iran (Zagros Mts.).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="705C51AD53F159E61DEDF6B08C93171B" pageId="14" pageNumber="83" type="notes">
<paragraph id="24529BCD62CD7223B3232ABE772317E2" pageId="14" pageNumber="83">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A3AAFED5C2CB6FFABA72DBEF1A6C1A9D" pageId="14" pageNumber="83">
Due to its sterile whorls of branches, this species seems very close to 
<taxonomicName id="672FEC466005CEA07CE690A6439351F6" authorityName="Soreng, Cabi &amp; L. J. Gillespie" authorityYear="2018" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Poa millii" order="Poales" pageId="14" pageNumber="83" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="millii">
<emphasis id="DFF7F370F6060D60844EB816FD7AB9F7" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="83">Poa millii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="ABA25D3A3591FD7DCA799686E26BD319" genus="P." lsidName="P. attalica" pageId="14" pageNumber="83" rank="species" species="attalica">
<emphasis id="DFAE616D9ED3B3F855F4DDD04499DDFD" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="83">P. attalica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but may be a derivative of 
<taxonomicName id="EBE301C7DDF998E93EE2B9E7F9A5CE3D" genus="P." lsidName="P. persica" pageId="14" pageNumber="83" rank="species" species="persica">
<emphasis id="B5A95162C49B230FE58D454CCA6A982E" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="83">P. persica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
since it has longer anthers than the previous taxa. Roshevits cited two gatherings of 
<emphasis id="0EE4D18E24E62467DF9C0E7E88617E4E" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="83">
<normalizedToken id="31DB1E9835793C2BA94FA48C5CF1E2BD" originalValue="Köie">Koeie</normalizedToken>
</emphasis>
: &quot;Kechwar, 700 m (3 May 1937; no. 475). Chah-Bazan, 500 m&quot; (Kechvar is about 60 km north of Dizful). The specimen at C has the same date and collection number as Roshevits cited and was annotated by Roshevits as this taxon; we select it as the lectotype. The anthers are ca. 1.1-1.2 mm as measured from the C photo and other characters seem to match 
<taxonomicName id="055F5C6A6206DCC6BCFB73E35B1D5103" genus="P." lsidName="P. attalica" pageId="14" pageNumber="83" rank="species" species="attalica">
<emphasis id="8E5F7AF8749BA00771E5EE01C67538F3" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="83">P. attalica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The anther length is given as 1.5 mm in 
<normalizedToken id="8B0B12DA184F260BF70C20FCC29FB6A9" originalValue="Roshevits’">Roshevits'</normalizedToken>
diagnosis. The specimen clearly has the hyaline lemma apices of 
<taxonomicName id="6601A655E4FBBF0C0DA638DDD3172CBD" genus="P." lsidName="P. persica" pageId="14" pageNumber="83" rank="species" species="persica">
<emphasis id="77135D239777E5944D779290A5AF3E2F" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="83">P. persica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
s.l. (in contrast to 
<taxonomicName id="606B8EEE6DE99BBDF89E08CEA20CF215" genus="P." lsidName="P. diaphora" pageId="14" pageNumber="83" rank="species" species="diaphora">
<emphasis id="18EA3DC9EEC39AA75BBB21AD5814B8F9" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="83">P. diaphora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). However, these features are also present in the type of 
<taxonomicName id="2224F06EFE33932FC9C20332362E1583" family="Poaceae" genus="E." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="E. capillaris" order="Poales" pageId="14" pageNumber="83" rank="species" species="capillaris">
<emphasis id="87DC68252909C8F41831E2029CFF7756" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="83">E. capillaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(= 
<taxonomicName id="3AB88090D44211A811D8E581E39A9395" genus="P." lsidName="P. millii" pageId="14" pageNumber="83" rank="species" species="millii">
<emphasis id="77930F78F219423D2BD916D73F89A854" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="83">P. millii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). 
<taxonomicName id="E2CCC44EF9703753B1BA9B3F9A46AC12" authorityName="Soreng, Cabi &amp; L. J. Gillespie" authorityYear="2018" baseAuthorityName="Soreng, Cabi &amp; L. J. Gillespie" baseAuthorityYear="2018" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Poa attalica" order="Poales" pageId="14" pageNumber="83" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="attalica">
<emphasis id="22AE121C611DA9F846929ACD13B99657" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="83">Poa attalica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has shorter anthers, ca. 0.8 to 1 mm, on the type (anthers not described by 
<bibRefCitation id="7226CDBA7A2D177D7EFD46A4D8998AEB" author="Scholz, H" journalOrPublisher="Willdenowia" pageId="22" pageNumber="91" pagination="33 - 36" refId="B48" refString="Scholz, H, 1980. Eine neue Eremopoa -Art (Gramineae) aus der Turkei. Willdenowia 10 (1): 33 - 36" title="Eine neue Eremopoa - Art (Gramineae) aus der Turkei." volume="10" year="1980">Scholz 1980</bibRefCitation>
or 
<bibRefCitation id="F6CEC0D16B934C6A7473829DC57DD87E" author="Mill, RR" journalOrPublisher="Opera Biologica" pageId="22" pageNumber="91" refId="B39" refString="Mill, RR, 1985. Eremopoa, Nephelochloa, Catabrosella, Colpodium, Hyalopoa, Catabrosa, Paracolpodium. In: Davis PH (Ed.) Flora of Turkey and East Aegean Islands, Vol. 9. Edinburgh University Press, Edinburgh, 486-501." title="Eremopoa, Nephelochloa, Catabrosella, Colpodium, Hyalopoa, Catabrosa, Paracolpodium. In: Davis PH (Ed.) Flora of Turkey and East Aegean Islands, Vol. 9. Edinburgh University Press, Edinburgh, 486 - 501." year="1985">Mill 1985</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="E91ECC6C4907B8D052B8CBE526E53E5E" authorityName="Soreng, Cabi &amp; L. J. Gillespie" authorityYear="2018" baseAuthorityName="Soreng, Cabi &amp; L. J. Gillespie" baseAuthorityYear="2018" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Poa nephelochloides" order="Poales" pageId="14" pageNumber="83" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nephelochloides">
<emphasis id="2C5AFABA614FBB148ACC32131B6400A4" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="83">Poa nephelochloides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="0B2AE9A4A23492E449132E9010081F51" genus="P." lsidName="P. attalica" pageId="14" pageNumber="83" rank="species" species="attalica">
<emphasis id="8E0164A0402A068CF49F76F51A31A3FA" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="83">P. attalica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may represent the same species, diagnosed as different from 
<taxonomicName id="0A60A8F5A56715E4A7933562C048497F" genus="P." lsidName="P. persica" pageId="14" pageNumber="83" rank="species" species="persica">
<emphasis id="FEF20D955127876B672674033A828D37" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="83">P. persica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by sterile branches and from 
<taxonomicName id="4FAE689FC9E8D1CF262E558AEC00C33A" authorityName="Boiss" authorityYear="1844" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Nephelochloa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Nephelochloa orientalis" order="Poales" pageId="14" pageNumber="83" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="orientalis">
<emphasis id="FF3BBE6939715901A09A52C46BA50C9C" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="83">Nephelochloa orientalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Boiss. by glabrous lemmas (
<taxonomicName id="4E588DCAB918F2608BD878A598D5BE43" genus="P." lsidName="P. nephelochloides" pageId="14" pageNumber="83" rank="species" species="nephelochloides">
<emphasis id="3EA82B7932D12BD6F0894C77404AA2BB" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="83">P. nephelochloides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has pubescent lemmas). However, 
<taxonomicName id="B4B93179B112C33229613C018E50C517" authorityName="Soreng, Cabi &amp; L. J. Gillespie" authorityYear="2018" baseAuthorityName="Soreng, Cabi &amp; L. J. Gillespie" baseAuthorityYear="2018" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Poa nephelochloides" order="Poales" pageId="14" pageNumber="83" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nephelochloides">
<emphasis id="8E8B3047C83DBBDB43C4C550A2356F36" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="83">Poa nephelochloides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="30019B9335764F36D1CF2C6D27289A14" genus="P." lsidName="P. attalica" pageId="14" pageNumber="83" rank="species" species="attalica">
<emphasis id="DC77E018436EA38FC9348CB046EBCC93" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="83">P. attalica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are geographically isolated by over 1500 km and have different anther lengths.
</paragraph>
